<item>
            <title>[LU-1857] Coverity: Fix &apos;Unbounded source buffer&apos; errors</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1857</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Thanks to the Coverity tool, we found some memory corruptions in the Lustre code, and more specifically cases of unbounded source buffers.&lt;br/&gt;
This is typically where we should use strncpy() instead of strcpy() or snprintf() instead of sprintf() because the size of the source buffer is not known.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will propose a patch to address the issues.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
